## CLI Command Structure

### Setup Commands (Onboarding & Scaffolding)
```bash
poolside setup              # Interactive wizard
poolside setup changelog    # Add GitHub Actions changelog workflow
poolside setup release      # Initialize release-config.json
poolside setup jira-pat     # Set up JIRA Personal Access Token
```

### Config Commands (Configuration Management)
```bash
poolside config             # Display all credentials and presets
poolside config show        # Same as 'config' (alias)
poolside config set <key> <value>  # Set a credential
poolside config get <key>   # Get a credential value
poolside config unset <key> # Remove a credential
poolside config test        # Test connections to all services
poolside config preset list         # List AI presets
poolside config preset use <name>   # Switch active preset
poolside config preset add <name>   # Add custom preset
poolside config preset remove <name> # Remove custom preset
```

### Workflow Commands
```bash
poolside process-epic <epic-id>   # Process JIRA epic
poolside process-issue <issue-id> # Process single JIRA issue
poolside list-epics <project-key> # List epics for project
poolside epic-status <epic-id>    # Get epic status
poolside cursor-prompt <epic-id>  # Generate Cursor prompt template
```

### Release Notes Commands
```bash
poolside generate-release-notes -c <config>  # Multi-repo release notes
poolside generate-single-repo -r <repo>      # Single repo (legacy)
```

### Changelog/Diff Commands
```bash
poolside changelog [options]  # Analyze git diff and generate summary
poolside diff [options]       # Alias for changelog
```

